t_text:
On June 23rd the UK voted to depart, but not for a specific destination. There is disagreement over what the destination should be, and whether any one destination has popular support.

This is the fundamental problem paralysing Brexit.

#BrexitVote #fbpe #pcpeu

@paul_trembath @PolhomeEditor No, we weren't. Nothing in that fudge says that Labour has become a Brexit- supporting or facilitating Party. Now, go away. Anyone still using that risible #PCPEU hashtag clearly isn't rational.

@ProfTimBale @jeremycorbyn @theresa_may @UKLabour That T-shirt though is as thoroughly stupid as the #PCPEU hashtag. It's two completely incompatible things. Corbyn is joined at the hip with a bigotry-driven Brexit, so supporting Corbyn means signing up to that stupidity, hatred and misery.
